    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
        <title>SIGNAL FUNCTION</title>
        <para>The service brake switch circuit function is to communicate to the ECM when the service brakes are applied
            and when the brakes are not applied. This information is used with cruise control and PTO operation, which
            are controlled by the ECM.
        </para>
